The average rate of change of \(f(x)\) on \([1,9]\) is

\[
\frac{f(9)-f(1)}{9-1}
=\frac{\bigl(9-2\sqrt{9}\bigr)-\bigl(1-2\sqrt1\bigr)}{8}
=\frac{(9-6)-(1-2)}{8}
=\frac{3-(-1)}{8}
=\frac{4}{8}
=\frac12.
\]

The average rate of change of \(f\) on \([5,a]\) is

\[
\frac{f(a)-f(5)}{a-5}
=\frac{\bigl(a^2+2a-8\bigr)-(25+10-8)}{a-5}
=\frac{a^2+2a-8-27}{a-5}
=\frac{a^2+2a-35}{a-5}
=\frac{(a+7)(a-5)}{a-5}
=a+7,
\]

for \(a\neq5\).  (If \(a=5\) the “interval” collapses and the average rate of change equals the derivative \(f'(5)=2\cdot5+2=12\), which agrees with \(a+7\) at \(a=5\).)
